Author: TREADWELL
Vol / Page: 47
Edition:
Quote: At last the [VD] situation became so bad that the men took into their own hands the task of cleaning up the [Cairo] brothel area, which consisted of one principal street and some minor ones, comprehensively called the Wasser. ... [48] The two raids, popularly known as the `Battles of the Wasser', were conducted with the object of preventing the continued misuse of the premises attacked.
